discovery_rule.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: Each entry corresponds to a single alarm configuration profile. Each profile contains a set of parameters for setting alarm thresholds for various performance attributes monitored at HDSL2/SHDSL segment endpoints. Profiles may be created/deleted using the row creation/deletion mechanism via hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileRowStatus. If an active entry is referenced in either hdsl2ShdslSpanConfAlarmProfile or hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfile, the entry MUST remain active until all references are removed.

discovery_rule.name: hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: Each entry corresponds to a single span configuration profile. Each profile contains a set of span configuration parameters. The configuration parameters in a profile are applied to those lines referencing that profile (see the hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfile object). Profiles may be created/deleted using the row creation/deletion mechanism via hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileRowStatus. If an active entry is referenced in hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfile, the entry MUST remain active until all references are removed.

discovery_rule.name: hdsl2ShdslUnitMaintEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: An entry in the hdsl2ShdslUnitMaintTable. Each entry corresponds to a single unit and is indexed by the ifIndex of the HDSL2/SHDSL line and the UnitId of the associated unit.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslMaintUnitPowerSource for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This object indicates the DC power source being used by the associated unit.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslMaintLoopbackTimeout for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This object configures the timeout value for loopbacks initiated at segments endpoints contained in the associated unit. A value of 0 disables the timeout.

discovery_rule.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: An entry in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintTable. Each entry corresponds to a single segment endpoint and is indexed by the ifIndex of the HDSL2/SHDSL line, the UnitId of the associated unit, and the side of the unit.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslMaintSoftRestart for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This object enables the manager to trigger a soft restart of the modem at the associated segment endpoint. The manager may only set this object to the 'restart(2)' value, which initiates a restart. The agent will perform a restart after approximately 5 seconds. Following the 5 second period, the agent will restore the object to the 'ready(1)' state.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslMaintPowerBackOff for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This object configures the receiver at the associated segment endpoint to operate in default or enhanced power backoff mode.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslMaintTipRingReversal for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This object indicates the state of the tip/ring pair at the associated segment endpoint.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslMaintLoopbackConfig for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This object controls configuration of loopbacks for the associated segment endpoint. The status of the loopback is obtained via the hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrStatus object.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalUAS for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Unavailable Seconds (UAS) during the 1-day interval as measured by hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalMoniSecs.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalLOSWS for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Loss of Sync Word (LOSW) Seconds during the 1-day interval as measured by hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalMoniSecs.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalCRCanomalies for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of CRC anomalies during the 1-day interval as measured by hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalMoniSecs.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalSES for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Severely Errored Seconds (SES) during the 1-day interval as measured by hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalMoniSecs.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalES for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Errored Seconds (ES) during the 1-day interval as measured by hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalMoniSecs.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalMoniSecs for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The amount of time in the 1-day interval over which the performance monitoring information is actually counted. This value will be the same as the interval duration except in a situation where performance monitoring data could not be collected for any reason.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalUAS for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Unavailable Seconds (UAS) during the interval.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalLOSWS for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Loss of Sync Word (LOSW) Seconds during the interval.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalCRCanomalies for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of CRC anomalies during the interval.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalSES for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Severely Errored Seconds (SES) during the interval.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalES for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Errored Seconds (ES) during the interval.

discovery_rule.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: An entry in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrTable. Each entry contains status and performance information relating to a single segment endpoint. It is indexed by the ifIndex of the HDSL2/SHDSL line, the UnitId of the associated unit, the side of the unit, and the wire pair of the associated modem.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrActivationState for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This object indicates the activation or training state of the wire pair.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrTipRingReversal for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This object indicates the state of the tip/ring for the wire pair.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayUAS for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Unavailable Seconds (UAS) during the current day as measured by hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayLOSWS for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Loss of Sync Word (LOSW) Seconds during the current day as measured by hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayCRCanomalies for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of CRC anomalies during the current day as measured by hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DaySES for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Severely Errored Seconds (SES) during the current day as measured by hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayES for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Errored Seconds (ES) during the current day as measured by hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayTimeElapsed for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current 1-day interval.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinUAS for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Unavailable Seconds (UAS) in the current 15-minute interval.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinLOSWS for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Loss of Sync Word (LOSW) Seconds in the current 15-minute interval.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinCRCanomalies for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of CRC anomalies in the current 15-minute interval.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinSES for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Severely Errored Seconds (SES) in the current 15-minute interval.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinES for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Errored Seconds (ES) in the current 15-minute interval.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinTimeElapsed for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Total elapsed seconds in the current 15-minute interval.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointUAS for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Unavailable Seconds (UAS) on this endpoint since the xU was last restarted.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointLOSWS for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Loss of Sync Word (LOSW) Seconds on this endpoint since the xU was last restarted.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCRCanomalies for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of CRC anomalies on this endpoint since the xU was last restarted.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointSES for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Severely Errored Seconds (SES) on this endpoint since the xU was last restarted.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointES for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Count of Errored Seconds (ES) on this endpoint since the xU was last restarted.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrStatus for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Contains the current state of the endpoint. This is a bit-map of possible conditions. The various bit positions are as follows: noDefect There are no defects on the line. powerBackoff Indicates enhanced Power Backoff. deviceFault Indicates that a vendor-dependent diagnostic or self-test fault has been detected. dcContinuityFault Indicates vendor-dependent conditions that interfere with span powering such as short and open circuits. snrMarginAlarm Indicates that the SNR margin has dropped below the alarm threshold. loopAttenuationAlarm Indicates that the loop attenuation exceeds the alarm threshold. loswFailureAlarm Indicates a forward LOSW alarm. configInitFailure Endpoint failure during initialization due to paired endpoint not able to support requested configuration. protocolInitFailure Endpoint failure during initialization due to incompatible protocol used by the paired endpoint. noNeighborPresent Endpoint failure during initialization due to no activation sequence detected from paired endpoint. loopbackActive A loopback is currently active at this segment endpoint. This is intended to supplement ifOperStatus. Note that there is a 1:1 relationship between the status bits defined in this object and the notification thresholds defined elsewhere in this MIB module.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrSnrMgn for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The current SNR margin for this endpoint as reported in a Status Response/SNR message.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrAtn for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The current loop attenuation for this endpoint as reported in a Network or Customer Side Performance Status message.

discovery_rule.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointConfEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: An entry in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointConfTable. Each entry represents a single segment endpoint in an HDSL2/SHDSL line. It is indexed by the ifIndex of the HDSL2/SHDSL line, the UnitId of the associated unit, the side of the unit, and the wire pair of the associated modem.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfile for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This object configures the alarm threshold values to be used for this segment endpoint. The values are obtained from the alarm configuration profile referenced by this object. The value of this object is the index of the referenced profile in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileTable, or NULL (a zero-length SnmpAdminString). If the value is a zero-length SnmpAdminString, the endpoint uses the default Alarm Configuration Profile for the associated span as per the hdsl2ShdslSpanConfAlarmProfile object in the hdsl2ShdslSpanConfTable. The default value of this object is a zero-length SnmpAdminString. Any attempt to set this object to a value that is not the value of the index for an active entry in the profile table, hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileTable, MUST be rejected.

discovery_rule.name: hdsl2ShdslInventoryEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: An entry in the hdsl2ShdslInventoryTable. Each entry represents inventory information for a single unit in an HDSL2/SHDSL line. It is indexed by the ifIndex of the HDSL2/SHDSL line and the Hdsl2ShdslUnitId of the associated unit.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslInvTransmissionModeCapability for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Contains the transmission mode capability of the SHDSL unit.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslInvVendorOther for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Other vendor information as reported in an Inventory Response message.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslInvEquipmentCode for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Equipment code conforming to ANSI T1.213, Coded Identification of Equipment Entities.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslInvVendorSoftwareVersion for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Vendor software version as reported in an Inventory Response message.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslInvVendorIssueNumber for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Vendor issue number as reported in an Inventory Response message.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslInvVendorListNumber for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Vendor list number as reported in an Inventory Response message.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslInvStandardVersion for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Version of the HDSL2/SHDSL standard implemented, as reported in an Inventory Response message.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslInvVendorEOCSoftwareVersion for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Vendor EOC version as reported in a Discovery Response message.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslInvVendorSerialNumber for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Vendor serial number as reported in an Inventory Response message.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslInvVendorModelNumber for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Vendor model number as reported in an Inventory Response message.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslInvVendorID for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Vendor ID as reported in an Inventory Response message.

discovery_rule.name: hdsl2ShdslSpanStatusEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: An entry in the hdsl2ShdslSpanStatusTable. Each entry represents the complete span in a single HDSL2/SHDSL line. It is indexed by the ifIndex of the associated HDSL2/SHDSL line.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslStatusActualPayloadRate for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Contains the actual line rate in this HDSL2/SHDSL span. Any framing overhead is not included.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslStatusMaxAttainablePayloadRate for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Contains the maximum attainable payload (user data) line rate in this HDSL2/SHDSL span. This object provides the maximum rate the line is capable of achieving. This is based upon measurements made during line probing. Any framing overhead is not included.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslStatusTransmissionModeCurrent for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Contains the current Power Spectral Density (PSD) regional setting of the HDSL2/SHDSL span.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslStatusActualLineRate for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Contains the actual line rate in this HDSL2/SHDSL span. This SHOULD equal ifSpeed. This rate includes payload (user data) and any applicable framing overhead

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslStatusMaxAttainableLineRate for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Contains the maximum attainable line rate in this HDSL2/SHDSL span. This object provides the maximum rate the line is capable of achieving. This is based upon measurements made during line probing. This rate includes payload (user data) and any applicable framing overhead.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslStatusNumAvailRepeaters for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Contains the actual number of repeaters/regenerators discovered in this HDSL2/SHDSL span.

discovery_rule.name: hdsl2ShdslSpanConfEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: An entry in the hdsl2ShdslSpanConfTable. Each entry represents the complete span in a single HDSL2/SHDSL line. It is indexed by the ifIndex of the associated HDSL2/SHDSL line.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslSpanConfAlarmProfile for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This object is a pointer to an alarm configuration profile in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileTable. The value of this object is the index of the referenced profile in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileTable. The alarm threshold configuration in the referenced profile will be used by default for all segment endpoints in this span. Individual endpoints may override this profile by explicitly specifying some other profile in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointConfTable. By default, this object will have the value 'DEFVAL' (the index of the default profile). Any attempt to set this object to a value that is not the value of the index for an active entry in the profile table, hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileTable, MUST be rejected.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfile for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This object is a pointer to a span configuration profile in the hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileTable, which applies to this span. The value of this object is the index of the referenced profile in the hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileTable. Note that span configuration profiles are only applicable to SHDSL lines. HDSL2 lines MUST reference the default profile, 'DEFVAL'. By default, this object will have the value 'DEFVAL' (the index of the default profile). Any attempt to set this object to a value that is not the value of the index for an active entry in the profile table, hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileTable, MUST be rejected.

item_prototype.name: hdsl2ShdslSpanConfNumRepeaters for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This object provisions the number of repeaters/regenerators in this HDSL2/SHDSL span.

item.name: SNMP Trap: HDSL2-SHDSL-LINE-MIB::hdsl2ShdslLocalPowerLoss
item.description:
This notification indicates impending unit failure due to loss of local power (last gasp).
Varbinds: 0. hdsl2ShdslInvVendorID (OCTETSTR) Vendor ID as reported in an Inventory Response message.

item.name: SNMP Trap: HDSL2-SHDSL-LINE-MIB::hdsl2ShdslnoNeighborPresent
item.description:
This notification indicates that the bit setting for noNeighborPresent in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrStatus object for this endpoint has changed.
Varbinds: 0. hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrStatus (BITS) Contains the current state of the endpoint. This is a bit-map of possible conditions. The various bit positions are as follows:
noDefect There are no defects on the line.
powerBackoff Indicates enhanced Power Backoff.
deviceFault Indicates that a vendor-dependent diagnostic or self-test fault has been detected.
dcContinuityFault Indicates vendor-dependent conditions that interfere with span powering such as short and open circuits.
snrMarginAlarm Indicates that the SNR margin has dropped below the alarm threshold.
loopAttenuationAlarm Indicates that the loop attenuation exceeds the alarm threshold.
loswFailureAlarm Indicates a forward LOSW alarm.
configInitFailure Endpoint failure during initialization due to paired endpoint not able to support requested configuration.
protocolInitFailure Endpoint failure during initialization due to incompatible protocol used by the paired endpoint.
noNeighborPresent Endpoint failure during initialization due to no activation sequence detected from paired endpoint.
loopbackActive A loopback is currently active at this segment endpoint.
This is intended to supplement ifOperStatus. Note that there is a 1:1 relationship between the status bits defined in this object and the notification thresholds defined elsewhere in this MIB module.

item.name: SNMP Trap: HDSL2-SHDSL-LINE-MIB::hdsl2ShdslLoopbackFailure
item.description:
This notification indicates that an endpoint maintenance loopback command failed for an HDSL2/SHDSL segment.
Varbinds: 0. hdsl2ShdslMaintLoopbackConfig (INTEGER) This object controls configuration of loopbacks for the associated segment endpoint. The status of the loopback is obtained via the hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrStatus object.

item.name: SNMP Trap: HDSL2-SHDSL-LINE-MIB::hdsl2ShdslSpanInvalidNumRepeaters
item.description:
This notification indicates that a mismatch has been detected between the number of repeater/regenerator units configured for an HDSL2/SHDSL line via the hdsl2ShdslSpanConfNumRepeaters object and the actual number of repeater/regenerator units discovered via the EOC.
Varbinds: 0. hdsl2ShdslSpanConfNumRepeaters (UNSIGNED32) This object provisions the number of repeaters/regenerators in this HDSL2/SHDSL span.

item.name: SNMP Trap: HDSL2-SHDSL-LINE-MIB::hdsl2ShdslPerfUASThresh
item.description:
This notification indicates that the unavailable seconds threshold (as per the hdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshUAS value) has been reached/exceeded for the HDSL2/SHDSL segment endpoint.
Varbinds: 0. hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinUAS (GAUGE) Count of Unavailable Seconds (UAS) in the current 15-minute interval.
1. hdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshUAS (UNSIGNED32) This object configures the threshold for the number of Unavailable Seconds (UAS) within any given 15-minute performance data collection interval. If the value of UAS in a particular 15-minute collection interval reaches/exceeds this value, an hdsl2ShdslPerfUASThresh MAY be generated. At most, one notification will be sent per interval per endpoint.

item.name: SNMP Trap: HDSL2-SHDSL-LINE-MIB::hdsl2ShdslPerfLOSWSThresh
item.description:
This notification indicates that the LOSW Seconds threshold (as per the hdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshLOSWS value) has been reached/exceeded for the HDSL2/SHDSL segment endpoint.
Varbinds: 0. hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinLOSWS (GAUGE) Count of Loss of Sync Word (LOSW) Seconds in the current 15-minute interval.
1. hdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshLOSWS (UNSIGNED32) This object configures the threshold for the number of Loss of Sync Word (LOSW) Seconds within any given 15-minute performance data collection interval.
